theorem Topology.P2_closure_iff_P3
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 (closure (A : Set X)) ↔ Topology.P3 A := by
  constructor
  · intro hP2
    exact Topology.P3_of_P2_closure (X := X) (A := A) hP2
  · intro hP3
    exact Topology.P2_of_P3_closure (X := X) (A := A) hP3

theorem Topology.closure_has_P2_of_denseInterior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Dense (interior A) → Topology.P2 (closure A) := by
  intro hDense
  -- For the closed set `closure A`, `P2` is equivalent to being open.
  have hEquiv :=
    Topology.P2_closure_iff_isOpen_closure (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Since `interior A` is dense, its closure is the whole space.
  have h_closure_int : closure (interior A) = (Set.univ : Set X) :=
    hDense.closure_eq
  -- Because `interior A ⊆ A ⊆ closure A`, we get `closure A = univ`.
  have h_univ_subset : (Set.univ : Set X) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) := by
    have h_mono : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (A : Set X) :=
      closure_mono (interior_subset : interior A ⊆ A)
    simpa [h_closure_int] using h_mono
  have h_closure_eq_univ : closure (A : Set X) = (Set.univ : Set X) := by
    apply Set.Subset.antisymm
    · intro _ _; simp
    · exact h_univ_subset
  -- Hence `closure A` is open (it equals `univ`).
  have hOpen : IsOpen (closure (A : Set X)) := by
    simpa [h_closure_eq_univ] using (isOpen_univ : IsOpen (Set.univ : Set X))
  -- Convert openness into `P2` using the equivalence.
  exact (hEquiv.2) hOpen

theorem Topology.P2_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    Topology.P2 (∅ : Set X) := by
  -- We reuse the existing result that the empty set satisfies all three properties.
  have h := Topology.empty_satisfies_P1_P2_P3 (X := X)
  exact h.2.1
